---

# 🧱 3. RESOLVER LAYER

This is subtle but extremely important.

Resolvers connect registries together.

Example:

```json id="qhx6r1"
"backgroundImageId": "bg_space"
```

becomes:

```txt id="uxgydn"
resolved asset object
```

during runtime hydration.

---

# 🧠 WHY THIS MATTERS

Resolvers allow:

* lazy loading
* caching
* asset swapping
* theme overrides
* localization later
* CDN migration later

without rewriting schema.

---

# 🧱 4. RUNTIME CONTEXT (VERY IMPORTANT)

This is the final hydrated object passed into GameRuntime.

Recommended shape:

```json id="jv4p93"
{
  "hunt": {},
  "registries": {},
  "runtimeState": {},
  "resolvedAssets": {},
  "metadata": {}
}
```

This becomes:

# the actual executable world state

